brazilian seafar ' strike damag oil export a strike by brazil 's 40,000 seafar who want pay rise of up to 180 pct may have cost the state-own oil compani petrobra 20 mln dlr in lost export order , the compani 's commerci director arthur de carvalho wa quot as say in press report . more than 170 ship in brazil , and about nine more in foreign port , have been halt by the strike , which began on februari 27. marin began blockad the ship on friday after the strike wa rule illeg , and some striker are run short of food , nation merchant marin union presid edson areia said .